      "id": "bug-015",
      "timestamp": "2026-06-07T18:32:00.000Z",
      "error_message": "Uncaught Error: Maximum update depth exceeded. ... at ThemeSync (src/app/providers.tsx)",
      "file": "apps/web/src/app/providers.tsx",
      "root_cause": "PRE-EXISTING. ThemeSync had two bidirectional effects (theme->store via update(); store->theme via setTheme()). When the persisted settings-store appTheme disagreed with next-themes theme on load (e.g. localStorage purechess-settings appTheme='dark' but next-themes theme='system'), the two effects ping-ponged forever and never converged -> React 'Maximum update depth exceeded'. ThemeSync is global in Providers so it crashed EVERY page including the untouched homepage. Browser-localStorage triggered (not caused by the game redesign); surfaces for any user whose stored appTheme differs from next-themes. Restarting the dev server did NOT fix it; clearing localStorage did (confirming the trigger).",
      "fix": "Replaced the two effects with ONE reconciliation effect + a lastSynced ref. Persisted store is source of truth (store->setTheme); next-themes changes mirror back to the store only when they did NOT originate from our own sync (ref guard breaks the echo). Verified live via chrome-devtools: appTheme='dark' + theme='system' loads with html data-theme=dark, store/next-themes both converge to dark, zero console errors, no loop. SettingsForm (sets both store+theme) and the (demo)/demo page (sets theme only) both still work.",
      "tags": [
        "next-themes",
        "theme-sync",
        "infinite-loop",
        "maximum-update-depth",
        "react",
        "providers",
        "pre-existing",
        "localstorage"
      ],
      "related_bugs": [
        "bug-014"
      ],
      "occurrences": 1,
      "last_seen": "2026-06-07T18:32:00.000Z"
    },
